Aged				KEY:Oracle ~ Aged						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You became an oracle late in life, or perhaps you aged and grew wise at an unnatural rate. You are a venerable member of your race. However, your physical abilities are affected as though you were old, rather than venerable.|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																														BONUS:STAT|STR,DEX|-2	BONUS:STAT|INT,WIS,CHA|1																																																																																								DESC:You became an oracle late in life, or perhaps you aged and grew wise at an unnatural rate. You are a venerable member of your race. However, your physical abilities are affected as though you were middle-aged, rather than venerable or old.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																															BONUS:STAT|STR,DEX|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																															DESC:You are immune to magical and non-magical disease.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																																		DESC:You will never die of old age and you are immune to death effects.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.1
Branded				KEY:Oracle ~ Branded					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse															DEFINE:OracleBrandedCursePenalty|0	BONUS:VAR|OracleBrandedCursePenalty|-2							DESC:You have a visible scar on your forehead or arm that depicts a mystical symbol of some significance. You had no choice in the matter; the brand appeared with fire and searing pain. Your brand cannot be disguised or altered, even with magic, although you can still benefit from cover or concealment, and you can cover it by wearing a hood or robe (as appropriate). Some NPCs may recognize the brand and become hostile, per the GM’s choice. As a supernatural ability, you can touch an enemy for 1d6+%1 fire damage; any opponent who takes damage bears your symbol until an equal amount of damage is healed. Any branded opponent takes %2 to save versus your spells and spell-like abilities. You can perform this branding touch %3 times per day.|(OracleCurseLVL/2)|OracleBrandedCursePenalty|(max(1,(CHA+1)))																																																																																																								DESC:You may add your Charisma bonus to your Fortitude saving throw bonus.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:SAVE|Fortitude|max(CHA,0)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																													DESC:You gain fire resistance 5.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,15																																																																																																																																	DESC:Your fire resistance increases to 10. The penalty branded opponents take increases to -4, and you may roll twice to overcome the SR of branded opponents.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15																																																					BONUS:VAR|OracleBrandedCursePenalty|-2|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15		SOURCEPAGE:p.1
Catatonic			KEY:Oracle ~ Catatonic					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse															DEFINE:OracleCatatonicCurseBonus|0	BONUS:VAR|OracleCatatonicCurseBonus|(OracleCurseLVL/5+1)		DESC:You seem lost in thought, responding slowly and unreliably to things happening around you. However, you see things others don’t. You have the staggered condition, and you suffer a -2 penalty to initiative. However, you are immune to confusion, and you receive a +%1 insight bonus to AC and saving throws during surprise rounds or when you are unaware of an attack.|OracleCatatonicCurseBonus																																																																																																											BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|-2	TEMPBONUS:PC|COMBAT|AC|OracleCatatonicCurseBonus|TYPE=Insight	TEMPBONUS:PC|SAVE|ALL|OracleCatatonicCurseBonus|TYPE=Insight																																																														DESC:You can not be caught flat-footed, and do not lose your Dexterity bonus to AC if your opponent is invisible, although you can still lose your Dexterity bonus to AC if immobilized. You can still be feinted.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			DESC:Spells you cast that normally have a casting time of 1 round can be cast as a standard action.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																							DESC:You are immune to mind-affecting and illusion effects.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15		SOURCEPAGE:p.1
Child				KEY:Oracle ~ Child						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse															DEFINE:OracleChildCurseSTRPenalty|0	BONUS:VAR|OracleChildCurseSTRPenalty|-4							DESC:You became an oracle early in life, and your body has remained that of a child. You take a %1 penalty to your Strength modifier for the purpose of Strength checks and your maneuver bonus, and gain a +2 bonus to Escape Artist and Stealth checks. Your age cannot be magically altered. NPCs may become friendly or unfriendly ( GM’s choice) depending on your behavior and the situation. Non-magical armor must be tailor-made for your, otherwise it can only be donned hastily, if it can be worn at all.|OracleChildCurseSTRPenalty																																																																									BONUS:VAR|CMB|OracleChildCurseSTRPenalty	BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist,Stealth|2																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				BONUS:VAR|OracleChildCurseSTRPenalty|2|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																											DESC:You gain a bonus revelation.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																								BONUS:VAR|OracleMysteryLevel|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																																					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Child Oracle Spell Choice|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15		SOURCEPAGE:p.1
Chilled				KEY:Oracle ~ Chilled					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You constantly ache and shiver, never able to get warm. You take a -2 penalty to all Dexterity– and Strength-based skill checks, and you can only run a number of rounds equal to your Charisma bonus (if it is lower than your Constitution score) before you must start making Constitution checks to continue running. You are immune to extremes of hot and cold. You add chill touch to your spells known.																																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|STAT.STR,STAT.DEX|-2	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Oracle=1|Chill Touch																																																																																		DESC:You are immune to the sickened condition. When you cast chill touch, you deal an additional %1 points of Strength damage, and may cast the spell at any spell level you can cast (as though it were modified with Heighten Spell, but without increased caster time).|(OracleCurseLVL/5)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																DESC:You have fire resistance %1. When you cast chill touch it does an additional %2 points of damage.|(OracleCurseLVL)|(CHA)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																	DESC:When you cast a spell that deals with the cold descriptor or of the necromancy school, you may roll twice to overcome SR taking the better result.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15		SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Choleric			KEY:Oracle ~ Choleric					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You are full of wrath, irritability and bitterness. Any time you take damage or lose an opposed skill check, you fly into a rage, as the spell, for 1d4+1 rounds. Each round, as a move action, you may make a Wisdom check (DC 15) to act normally. You gain a +4 bonus to save against poisons and emotion effects.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			DESC:Add rage to your spells known as a 2nd level spell.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																														SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Oracle=2|Rage|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																													DESC:You can treat any weapon you wield, even a ranged weapon, as having the vicious magic weapon property. You can use this ability as a free action %1 rounds per day, which need not be consecutive. If you affect multiple weapons, you must expend a round of use for each weapon (or end of a double weapon) you want to modify in this fashion.|(OracleCurseLVL)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																						DESC:You can cast spells and use spell-like abilities while under the effects of a rage effect (as the spell or barbarian class ability).|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15			SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Feral				KEY:Oracle ~ Feral						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:There is something of the animal in you. You relate better to beasts than to “people.” You suffer a -4 penalty on Diplomacy checks. For purposes of spells, weapon qualities, and other effects, you can be counted as animal or your actual type (though spells that grant intelligence to an animal, such as awaken, do not work on you), whichever is least advantageous for you. You gain wild empathy, as a druid of your curse level.																																																																																																	BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|-4	ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Wild Empathy	BONUS:VAR|WildEmpathyLVL|OracleCurseLVL																																																																								DESC:You can use wild shape, %1 time per day, as a druid, to become an animal. This functions as|min((OracleCurseLVL/5),3)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	DESC:Beast Shape I|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,10	DESC:Beast Shape II|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,15	DESC:Beast Shape III|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	DESC:for its effects.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Druid ~ Wild Shape|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|DruidWildShape|OracleCurseLVL|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5		BONUS:VAR|WildShapeTimes|min((OracleCurseLVL/5),3)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Foretold			KEY:Oracle ~ Foretold					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:Your life fulfills the predictions of one or more important prophesies. You may choose to embrace, or resist, your foretold fate. Subtract your curse level from the DC of gather information or Knowledge checks to learn things about you. You suffer a -10 penalty to Will saves versus non-mind-affecting spells and spell-like abilities of the divination school. Once per day, you can “take 10” on a check even you would not normally be able to do so because of distractions or threats.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Foretold Oracle Spell Choice|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																								DESC:You gain a bonus revelation.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																								BONUS:VAR|OracleMysteryLevel|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																																					SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Oracle=8|Screen|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Forsaken			KEY:Oracle ~ Forsaken					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You are beyond the salvation of others, but endure to give aid and warning. Others cannot use the aid another action to help you, you do not gain a bonus to hit by flanking, and you cannot benefit from feats, abilities, or spells that allow someone else to become a target of an attack or take damage in your place. However, you gain a +4 on saves versus all environmental conditions, including hunger and thirst, and you always stabilize from dying.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Forsaken Oracle Spell Choice|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																								DESC:You can return from the dead once per week as a supernatural ability, as though the spell Raise Dead were cast on you with caster level %1. This occurs 1d6 hours after you die.|(OracleCurseLVL)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,15																																																																																								DESC:You can return from the dead once per week as a supernatural ability, as though the spell Resurrection were cast on you with caster level %1. This occurs 1d6 hours after you die.|(OracleCurseLVL)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Frenetic			KEY:Oracle ~ Frenetic					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You are frenetic and excited, never pausing. You can never take “take 10” on a skill check, and you take a -2 morale penalty when you “take 20.” However, you roll initiative twice, taking the better result.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													DESC:You add your Charisma bonus to your Reflex saving throws.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:SAVE|Reflex|CHA|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																															DESC:You gain the Wind Stance feat, even if you don't qualify for the prerequisites.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																											ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Wind Stance|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																	DESC:Roll initiative three times, instead of twice, taking the best result. You gain the Lightning Stance feat, even if you don't qualify for the prerequisites.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15																																																				ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Lightning Stance|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Friendless			KEY:Oracle ~ Friendless					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse															DEFINE:OracleFriendlessCurseBonus|0																	DESC:Alone and despised, you draw power from your inner resolve. You do not gain your Charisma bonus to Diplomacy checks, and if you use Diplomacy to make a request of someone, their attitude worsens one step (but no worse than unfriendly) after the request succeeds or fails. However, you gain your Charisma bonus to Sense Motive checks and saving throws versus spells and spell-like abilities of the enchantment school, in addition to your Wisdom.																																																																																													BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|-CHA	BONUS:SKILL|Sense Motive|CHA																																																																																						DESC:You have a +%1 morale bonus to Disguise, Intimidate, and Stealth checks, and always treat those as class skills.|OracleFriendlessCurseBonus|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Disguise,Intimidate,Stealth|OracleFriendlessCurseBonus|TYPE=Morale|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|OracleFriendlessCurseBonus|3|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Friendless Curse Class Skills|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																										DESC:You are constantly protected as per the spell Nondetection.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																BONUS:VAR|OracleFriendlessCurseBonus|3|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																DESC:You are constantly protected as per the spell Mind Blank|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Friendless Curse Class Skills								CATEGORY:Internal																														CSKILL:Disguise|Intimidate|Stealth		SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Infested			KEY:Oracle ~ Infested					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:Your body is full of writhing parasites, which occasionally burst forth through your skin, mouth, and eyes. You tend to inspire repulsion, pity, and disgust in others. You take a -4 penalty on Charisma-based skill checks. On the upside, you cannot be further infested by other parasites, being immune to parasitic infestations, implantation of eggs or organisms, or attachment by blood drinkers. Such attempts either assimilate into your existing parasites, doing no further harm, or are simply unsuccessful. You are immune to the attacks of rot grub swarms.																																																																	BONUS:SKILL|STAT.CHA|-4																																																																																															DESC:You are also immune to the sickened condition.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5|PREVARLT:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				DESC:You are also immune to the sickened and nauseated conditions.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																																DESC:As a standard action you can summon a grub swarm, which appears adjacent to you. The swarm will attack anyone (other than you) in its space but is otherwise stationary and does not pursue creatures. The swarm dissipates after %1 minute(s), crawling into your body or withering into gore and slime. You may use this ability once per day.|OracleCurseLVL|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Melancholy			KEY:Oracle ~ Melancholy					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You are prone to anguish and inward-turning. The phantasmagoria of your despair has inured you to transient suffering. You are always shaken, but immune to being frightened or panicked.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Melancholy Oracle Spell Choice|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																								DESC:You are immune to emotion effects. You take no morale bonuses or penalties.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																																																																												DESC:You gain the supernatural ability to inflict despair in others. As a free action, you can make all opponents within 30 feet become shaken for one minute. This ability cannot cause a shaken opponent to become frightened.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Merciful			KEY:Oracle ~ Merciful					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You are bound to offer tender aid to those who are most wounded. If a non-enemy character who is adjacent asks you to heal them, or asks you for help and you can tell they have taken damage or drain or suffer from a disease or poison, you must help them on your next tum. If they have a condition or suffer from a poison or disease that you can neutralize or cure with any ability you possess or any spell you can cast, you must do so as your next action. Otherwise, if they have taken any damage, you must cast a spell or use an ability that heals hit points. Also, you cannot perform a coup de grace. You gain the ability to lay on hands, as the paladin ability, using your curse level as your paladin level.																											ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Paladin ~ Lay on Hands	BONUS:VAR|LayOnHandsLVL|max(2,OracleCurseLVL)																																																																											DESC:You gain a mercy, as the paladin ability.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																	ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Paladin ~ Mercy|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|Mercies|1-min(MercyLVL/3,6)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|MercyLVL|OracleCurseLVL|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																								DESC:You gain a second mercy, and can exchange your first mercy for a different one.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																											BONUS:VAR|Mercies|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																				DESC:You gain a third mercy, and can exchange one of your existing mercies for a different one.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15																																																																				BONUS:VAR|Mercies|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Odious				KEY:Oracle ~ Odious						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:Your skin reeks with an acrid, foul stench, bringing low all those who must endure your smell. You have the stench quality. You suffer a -4 penalty on Diplomacy checks against any creature that lacks the stench quality.																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:SITUATION|Diplomacy=Against creatures that lack stench quality|-4																																																																																			DESC:You can hold your breath as a free action when it’s not your turn, before anything affects you.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Oracle=3|Stinking Cloud|Oracle=5|Insect Plague|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																									DESC:You are immune to all diseases, non-magical and magical.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Phlegmatic			KEY:Oracle ~ Phlegmatic					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:Your spirit is unhurried and you move only with purpose and after due deliberation. Your initiative check result is limited to %1, but you can never be made flat-footed. You can still lose your Dexterity bonus to AC if you are immobilized, or if an opponent feints you or is invisible.|(OracleCurseLVL)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Phlegmatic Oracle Spell Choice|1|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																																																																								DESC:Any time you move no more than 5 feet in a round, you gain a luck bonus of %1 to AC. This luck bonus to AC improves your CMD as well.|(min(CHA,(OracleCurseLVL/2)))|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																						TEMPBONUS:PC|COMBAT|AC|(min(CHA,(OracleCurseLVL/2)))|TYPE=Luck|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																										DESC:You are immune to fear.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Ravenous			KEY:Oracle ~ Ravenous					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:OracleClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.OracleCurse																																								DESC:You suffer from ravenous hunger, but cannot hold down large meals. You are almost impossibly thin, your tendons and bones clearly visible beneath your loose skin. You can only go one day without food before you begin to starve. You cannot eat for more than one ten minutes at a time before you must wait half an hour to eat again. However, your nonlethal damage total from starvation and thirst cannot exceed your hit points and you are immune to all ingested poisons and harmful potions.																																																																																																																																																																																						DESC:You gain a primary bite attack that deals damage for a creature of your size (ld6 for a Medium character, ld4 for Small). You have the grab ability; if you hit with this bite, you deal normal damage and attempt to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. You receive a +4 bonus on combat maneuver checks made to start and maintain a grapple. You gain the swallow whole ability; the AC of your stomach is %1, and it has %2 hit points. If you swallow whole an opponent of any size, they disgorge 2d4 rounds later on your turn automatically, nauseating you for your turn.|(10+(AC_Natural_Armor/2)+CHA)|(HP/10)|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																											ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Ravenous Curse Natural Attacks|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|CMB_Grapple|4|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Grab|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5	ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Swallow Whole|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,5																																																																																																																																					DESC:You learn Heroes' Feast as a 5th level spell, though you are unable to benefit from it|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																																																																									SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Oracle=5|Heroes' Feast|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,10																															DESC:Your swallow whole ability allows you to swallow opponents up to your own size.|PREVARGTEQ:OracleCurseLVL,15	SOURCEPAGE:p.4
